    <string name="help_title">Help</string>
    <string name="help_subtitle">Quick overview of navigation, data flow and diagnostics.</string>
    <string name="help_login_label">Login</string>
    <string name="help_login_text">Sign-in uses Bosch SingleKey ID and Bosch eBike Data Act access. After successful sign-in, the app opens the main navigation.</string>
    <string name="help_activities_label">Activities</string>
    <string name="help_activities_text">The tour list loads locally cached activities first and refreshes in the background when needed. Filters, sorting and search operate directly on the loaded list.</string>
    <string name="help_bike_label">Account</string>
    <string name="help_bike_text">The account area shows linked Bosch Smart System bikes together with Bosch account and OIDC details such as UserInfo, discovery metadata and signing certificate information. Bike data remains cache-first from Room. Bosch eBike System 2 and eBike Connect are not supported.</string>
    <string name="help_functions_label">Functions</string>
    <string name="help_functions_text">CSV and PDF exports use only activities, detail data and account metadata already stored in the local cache, then open the Android share sheet. The CSV format preset from Setup controls separators, decimal numbers and date formatting; the PDF report always follows the active system locale.</string>
    <string name="help_statistics_label">Statistics</string>
    <string name="help_statistics_text">The statistics screen aggregates all locally cached activities into weekly or monthly totals for distance, ride time and tour count. Tour counts appear as labels directly on each bar, average distance and average ride-time guide lines provide orientation, and the summary tiles also show average values per tour. A separate highlights and rhythm section below the chart surfaces longest tour, elevation gain, speed, rider power, calories, effective travel speed, favorite weekday and weekly riding frequency from the same cached activity set. Tap any period to expand the aggregated values below the chart. The refresh button in the top bar triggers a cloud sync that automatically updates the chart once new data arrives.</string>
    <string name="help_diagnostics_label">Diagnostics</string>
    <string name="help_diagnostics_text">The API test screen remains available as a diagnostic tool and is intentionally not part of the primary navigation.</string>

